paragraphs.title: Load Vaccine Batch Data
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.mllib.regression.LabeledPoint
import org.apache.spark.mllib.regression.LinearRegressionModel
import org.apache.spark.mllib.regression.LinearRegressionWithSGD
import org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.Vectors
import java.text.NumberFormat

val data = sqlContext.read.json("/demo/data/Biologics/biologicsTraining.csv")
data.cache
data.registerTempTable("data")
data.printSchema
data.show

case class Vec (temp: Double, glucose: Double, lac: Double, ph: Double, oxy: Double, cells: Double, batch: Int, time: Int)

/* 
val row = data.map(x=> Vec( 
        x.select(internalTemp), // temp
        x.select(glucose), // glucose
        x.select(lactate), // lac
        x.select(phLevel), // ph
        x.select(oxygenLevel), // oxy
        x.select(cellsPerML), // cells
        x.select(batchNumber),   // batch
        x.select(hoursFromStart)    // time
    )
)

row.toDF.registerTempTable("row")
//sample(true, 0.03)
*/

// create feature vector
val trainingDataRDD = data.map { x=> LabeledPoint(x.getAs[Double]("cellsPerML"),
    Vectors.dense(x.getAs[Double]("glucoseLevel"), x.getAs[Double]("lactateLevel"), x.getAs[Double]("phLevel"), x.getAs[Double]("disolvedOxygen"), x.getAs[Long]("hoursFromStart"))) 
}

trainingDataRDD.take(40).foreach(println)

// Building the model
var numIterations = 30
var stepSize = 0.0001
val linearModel = LinearRegressionWithSGD.train(trainingDataRDD, numIterations, stepSize)

// Evaluate model on training examples and compute training error
val valuesAndPreds = trainingDataRDD .map { 
    point => val prediction = linearModel.predict(point.features)
    (point.label, prediction)
}
val MSE = valuesAndPreds.map{case(v, p) => math.pow((v - p), 2)}.mean()
println("training Mean Squared Error = " +  NumberFormat.getInstance().format(MSE) )

paragraphs.title: Visualize Key Feature Relationship
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select glucoseLevel, lactateLevel as lactateLevel, phLevel, disolvedOxygen*10 as oxygen, cellsPerML/100000 as cellDensity, hoursFromStart, batchNumber from data where batchNumber <= 5

paragraphs.title: Visualize Cell Density Growth by Batch
Create Training Data Set

val forecast0 = sqlContext.sql("SELECT A.batchNumber, " + 
                               "B.cellsPerML," + 
                               //"A.cellsPerML, " + 
                               "A.disolvedOxygen, " + 
                               "A.glucoseLevel, " + 
                               "A.lactateLevel, " + 
                               "A.phLevel " +  
                               "FROM (SELECT batchNumber, hoursFromStart, cellsPerML, disolvedOxygen, glucoseLevel, lactateLevel, phLevel FROM data) as A, " + 
                               "     (SELECT batchNumber, hoursFromStart, cellsPerML FROM data) as B " +
                               "WHERE A.hoursFromStart = 108 AND B.hoursFromStart = 168 AND A.batchNumber = B.batchNumber")
forecast0.show
forecast0.cache

val forecastRDD = forecast0.map { x=> LabeledPoint(x.getAs[Double]("cellsPerML"),
    Vectors.dense(x.getAs[Double]("glucoseLevel"), x.getAs[Double]("lactateLevel"), x.getAs[Double]("phLevel"), x.getAs[Double]("disolvedOxygen"))) 
}

forecastRDD.cache
forecastRDD.take(30).foreach(println)
